divorce in this state

197
00:13:03,640 --> 00:13:08,384
are absence of a spouse, incurable
insanity, life imprisonment or adultery.

198
00:13:08,634 --> 00:13:10,686
Well, he hasn't
been faithful.

199
00:13:10,776 --> 00:13:13,133
Do you have any witnesses
or corroboration?

200
00:13:14,250 --> 00:13:15,186
Not really.

201
00:13:15,187 --> 00:13:18,121
It wouldn't matter anyway
with both parties at fault.

202
00:13:18,954 --> 00:13:23,836
- N-No. We haven't-- we aren't--
- Ken. Ken, what are you doing?

203
00:13:23,930 --> 00:13:26,522
You think the governor needs
another scandal on the ticket?

204
00:13:28,718 --> 00:13:33,039
I am sorry for presuming,
Mrs. Draper. That was wrong.

205
00:13:35,219 --> 00:13:36,648
So what do I do?

206
00:13:36,746 --> 00:13:38,110
I know it's hard
to understand,

207
00:13:38,111 --> 00:13:41,047
but the state of New York doesn't want
<i>anyone to get divorced.</i>

208
00:13:41,328 --> 00:13:43,008
That's why people
go to Reno.

209
00:13:43,245 --> 00:13:44,822
It's painless.

210
00:13:45,510 --> 00:13:47,009
I met my second wife.

211
00:13:47,518 --> 00:13:50,123
You stay there for six weeks
to establish residency.

212
00:13:50,124 --> 00:13:54,315
Mr. Draper doesn't even need to go,
just consent.

213
00:13:55,135 --> 00:13:56,293
I see.

214
00:13:56,294 --> 00:13:59,423
