You always do.

241
00:15:29,218 --> 00:15:30,264
Lane.

242
00:15:32,732 --> 00:15:33,795
Yes?

243
00:15:33,935 --> 00:15:35,232
Don't be disheartened.

244
00:15:35,733 --> 00:15:37,825
I'll put in
a good word for you.

245
00:15:38,836 --> 00:15:42,545
- Thank you.
- No, thank you.

246
00:16:23,042 --> 00:16:25,853
We've got a month till winter,
then we'll be set.

247
00:16:26,326 --> 00:16:28,781
This is what I showed
the man from the bank today.

248
00:16:29,807 --> 00:16:32,091
What are they gonna do,
sell this place?

249
00:16:32,291 --> 00:16:35,810
The bank's gonna get their
payday right after me.

250
00:16:36,628 --> 00:16:38,905
We got nothing and we're about
to have less.

251
00:16:38,906 --> 00:16:39,970
Fine!

252
00:16:40,625 --> 00:16:44,367
I'll sell. I'll sell my crop
for nothing.

253
00:16:45,874 --> 00:16:46,756
Dick.

254
00:16:46,757 --> 00:16:50,760
- What are you doing?
- I'll drive it to Chicago tonight.

255
00:16:50,761 --> 00:16:52,133
You're drunk.

256
00:16:58,561 --> 00:17:00,671
Go.
He can barely stand.

257
00:17:03,175 --> 00:17:04,266
Calm down.

258
00:17:06,890 --> 00:17:07,959
Here.

259
00:17:09,552 --> 00:17:10,722
Calm down.

260
00:17:13,801 --> 00:17:15,158
It ain't gonna rain.

261
00:17:33,057 --> 00:17:36,611
Pa! Daddy! Daddy!

262
00:18:12,146 --> 00:18:13,885
Your guests have arrived.

263
00:18:16,711 --> 00:18:18,022
Close the door.
Have a seat.

264
00:18:19,839 --> 00:18:22,535
- What's he doing here?
- You gonna read us your will?

265
00:18:22,536 --> 00:18:25,298
- I want the Cadillac.
- I couldn't sleep.

266
00:18:26,181 --> 00:18:29,777
And I thought, why don't
we go to McCann directly?

267
00:18:29,778 --> 00:18:31,866
Because you can't. It's done.

268
00:18:31,867 --> 00:18:34,805
- You're not even gonna ask?
- I did, yesterday.

269
00:18:35,519 --> 00:18:38,490
And you were right--
P.P.L. <i>is</i> being sold,

270
00:18:38,588 --> 00:18:41,166
So it seems we're all
going to McCann.

271
00:18:41,308 --> 00:18:42,849
They cut you loose.

272
00:18:43,208 --> 00:18:45,853
I want you to find out what the price was
and give us a shot.

273
00:18:45,854 --> 00:18:47,128
Enough.

274
00:18:47,467 --> 00:18:50,135
I should fire you for even trying 
to involve me in this conspiracy.

275
00:18:50,136 --> 00:18:52,168
Go ahead. It's the only thing
you did well here.

276
00:18:52,169 --> 00:18:55,446
- Don, let it go.
- I did a great many things here.

277
00:18:58,297 --> 00:19:01,619
<i>Have another. It's 9:30
for god's sake.</i>

278
00:19:03,914 --> 00:19:05,336
Jes, that's right.

279
00:19:07,888 --> 00:19:11,008
You have absolute authority
to fire anyone.

280
00:19:14,043 --> 00:19:15,229
Fire us.

281
00:19:18,245 --> 00:19:20,827
Fire us. Sever our contracts.
Let us go.

282
00:19:23,222 --> 00:19:25,901
- Can you do that?
- Why would I?

283
00:19:25,923 --> 00:19:27,683
Because once this sale
goes through, 

284
00:19:27,684 --> 00:19:30,885
you'll be thrown overboard and you'll be
a corpse knocking against their hull.

285
00:19:30,886 --> 00:19:33,190
Nothing good ever came
from seeking revenge.

286
00:19:33,191 --> 00:19:35,339
Nonsense.
We'll make you a partner.

287
00:19:39,182 --> 00:19:41,858
I should think this
is worth more than that.

288
00:19:43,360 --> 00:19:47,338
So we're negotiating.
We'll put your name on the door.

289
00:19:47,339 --> 00:19:48,387
I don't know.

290
00:19:48,388 --> 00:19:50,871
- Do you know how to do what he does?
- I don't.

291
00:19:58,902 --> 00:20:02,375
It could be done,
But getting you--

292
00:20:02,376 --> 00:20:05,442
us out of here isn't
the difficult part.

293
00:20:05,911 --> 00:20:09,374
- We need accounts.
- Let's say we have Lucky Strike.

294
00:20:10,657 --> 00:20:14,521
And although that's, let's see,
$23 million in Billings--

295
00:20:14,522 --> 00:20:15,702
24.

296
00:20:16,237 --> 00:20:19,080
We'd still need another
third for cash flow.

297
00:20:19,081 --> 00:20:21,814
I can't take anyone else
or Lee Garner sr.

298
00:20:21,815 --> 00:20:23,157
Won't think that he's special.

299
00:20:23,158 --> 00:20:26,193
- What about Hilton?
- No.

300
00:20:26,194 --> 00:20:28,459
Can we get any
of our other accounts?

301
00:20:28,595 --> 00:20:29,801
We'll get them.

302
00:20:31,038 --> 00:20:33,087
If I were to send
a telex in at noon today

303
00:20:33,088 --> 00:20:34,843
That you've all
been sacked,

304
00:20:34,942 --> 00:20:36,721
It's after close
of business in London.

305
00:20:36,722 --> 00:20:41,570
It would remain unnoticed until Monday 
morning there--2:00 A.M. here.

306
00:20:41,767 --> 00:20:43,844
That gives us today
and the weekend

307
00:20:43,845 --> 00:20:48,142
To first gather accounts and then 
a skeleton staff to service them. 

308
00:20:48,612 --> 00:20:51,038
And of course we would have
to obtain all 

309
00:20:51,039 --> 00:20:53,734
the materials required for continuity
of service.

310
00:20:54,401 --> 00:20:57,381
Obtain? We he to steal
everything.

311
00:20:59,441 --> 00:21:01,909
Anyone approached
must be a certainty.

312
00:21:03,097 --> 00:21:05,441
If news spreads,
they'll lock us out.

313
00:21:10,754 --> 00:21:12,221
Do we vote
or something?

314
00:21:18,361 --> 00:21:23,045
Well, gentlemen, I suppose you're fired.

315
00:21:25,403 --> 00:21:26,845
We'll, it's official.

316
00:21:27,061 --> 00:21:29,645
Friday,
December 13th, 1963--

317
00:21:30,798 --> 00:21:32,871
Four guys shot
their own legs off.

318
00:21:35,537 --> 00:21:37,042
Allison,
Mr. Pryce has requested

319
00:21:37,043 --> 00:21:39,747
an office-wide memo--
"the office is closed this weekend.

320
00:21:39,748 --> 00:21:42,268
"all work is suspended.
Carpet cleaning."

321
00:21:42,389 --> 00:21:45,653
- Can you get me Mr. Campbell?
- He didn't come in today. He's sick.

322
00:21:45,654 --> 00:21:47,403
Call his house.
It's important.

323
00:21:47,404 --> 00:21:48,920
Peggy, my office.

324
00:21:52,535 --> 00:21:53,785
What do I bring?

325
00:21:58,223 --> 00:22:00,059
Shut the door.
Sit down.

326
00:22:05,288 --> 00:22:08,014
I know we have to roll out
Western Union by New Year's.

327
00:22:08,204 --> 00:22:10,768
I don't have art.
There's no one there.

328
00:22:10,984 --> 00:22:12,420
they're selling
the company.

329
00:22:13,422 --> 00:22:14,595
Again?

330
00:22:15,296 --> 00:22:16,984
I'm starting
a new agency.

331
00:22:17,275 --> 00:22:19,141
I need you here Sunday evening
to get your things

332
00:22:19,142 --> 00:22:22,312
And to help us collect
whatever accounts we end up taking.

333
00:22:22,317 --> 00:22:24,101
- Really?
- Yes.

334
00:22:25,195 --> 00:22:26,639
Who else is going?

335
00:22:26,969 --> 00:22:30,345
Why do you need to know that?
Because it's important.

336
00:22:30,346 --> 00:22:33,937
I can't tell you. Peggy, we are being
bought my McCann.

337
00:22:33,938 --> 00:22:35,393
Do you know
what that means?

338
00:22:35,783 --> 00:22:38,672
You just assume I'll do
whatever you say...

339
00:22:40,353 --> 00:22:43,663
Just follow you
like some nervous poodle.

340
00:22:44,728 --> 00:22:47,733
- I'm not going to beg you.
- Beg me? You didn't even ask me.

341
00:22:50,180 --> 00:22:52,922
Fine, I'm asking you.

342
00:22:54,071 --> 00:22:56,423
I've had other offers,
you know,

343
00:22:57,114 --> 00:22:59,988
that came with a sales pitch
about opportunity.

344
00:23:01,398 --> 00:23:03,565
Everyone thinks
you do all my work.

345
00:23:05,456 --> 00:23:06,659
Even you.

346
00:23:11,366 --> 00:23:13,867
I don't want to make a career
out of being there

347
00:23:13,868 --> 00:23:16,235
so you can kick me
when you fail.

348
00:23:17,741 --> 00:23:19,910
I guess I'll have to talk
to Kurt and Smitty.

349
00:23:20,865 --> 00:23:22,009
I guess so.

350
00:23:34,313 --> 00:23:38,308
- <i>Where the hell are my pajamas?</i>
- Will you please relax?

351
00:23:39,138 --> 00:23:43,238
Trudy, I called in sick today
because I had my interview with Ogilvy.

352
00:23:43,239 --> 00:23:45,793
- I have to look sick.
- You do.

353
00:23:56,749 --> 00:23:58,283
What a pleasant surprise.

354
00:23:59,030 --> 00:24:00,275
Sorry to drop in.

355
00:24:01,304 --> 00:24:04,056
- <i>How are you?</i>
- <i>Better than my husband.</i>

356
00:24:05,228 --> 00:24:08,129
And how are you?
We've been calling all day.

357
00:24:08,130 --> 00:24:10,534
- <i>May I take your coats?</i>
- <i>We're fine.</i>

358
00:24:13,710 --> 00:24:15,618
I'm going to change
the sheets.

359
00:24:27,599 --> 00:24:32,254
- Is everything okay?
- McCann bought P.P.L. and us.

360
00:24:33,036 --> 00:24:36,730
- What? Again?
- We need to talk to you.

361
00:24:36,731 --> 00:24:39,677
- It's serious.
- We're not firing you.

362
00:24:39,948 --> 00:24:43,950
Oh, am I getting a few more
adjectives added to my title?

363
00:24:45,298 --> 00:24:47,661
Don't bother.
I have other plans.

364
00:24:47,662 --> 00:24:49,798
<i>Peter, may I speak</i>
<i>to you for a moment?</i>

365
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:55,007
Pete, we're starting
a new agency.

366
00:24:56,362 --> 00:24:58,520
We're here to talk
to you about joining us.

367
00:24:59,804 --> 00:25:02,687
Wait a minute.
They're letting you go?

368
00:25:03,208 --> 00:25:05,768
Keep it to yourself,
but I'm taking American Tobacco.

369
00:25:06,347 --> 00:25:10,845
We need another $7-$10 million
in billings for cash flow or something.

370
00:25:11,083 --> 00:25:13,218
What do you have in
your saddlebag so far?

371
00:25:13,820 --> 00:25:15,834
I don't have
a saddlebag.

372
00:25:16,290 --> 00:25:18,046
I don't know what
you're talking about.

373
00:25:18,704 --> 00:25:21,773
Pete, I don't blame you for bailing out
the way you've been treated.

374
00:25:24,011 --> 00:25:27,861
- So Kenny turned you down?
- We haven't spoken to Ken... yet.

375
00:25:28,520 --> 00:25:32,110
And yes, we want your accounts,
but we also want your talent.

376
00:25:32,423 --> 00:25:37,849
- Really? And what are my talents?
- You'll do what it takes.

377
00:25:37,850 --> 00:25:42,806
No, I want to hear it
from <i>him.</i>

378
00:25:46,840 --> 00:25:48,857
It's not hard
for me to say, Pete.

379
00:25:49,458 --> 00:25:51,784
You saw this coming,
we didn't.

380
00:25:52,886 --> 00:25:56,020
<i>In fact, you've been ahead</i>
<i>on a lot of things--</i>

381
00:25:56,839 --> 00:26:00,862
Aeronautics, teenagers,
the negro market.

382
00:26:02,176 --> 00:26:04,728
We need you to keep us
looking <i>forward.</i>

383
00:26:07,597 --> 00:26:09,129
I do, anyway.

384
00:26:12,106 --> 00:26:15,819
I want to be a partner
and I want my name in the lobby.

385
00:26:18,438 --> 00:26:19,904
There's not
gonna be a lobby.

386
00:26:28,026 --> 00:26:30,701
North American Aviation,
Secor laxatives,

387
00:26:30,702 --> 00:26:33,768
Gillette, Jai Alai,
maybe Pampers--

388
00:26:34,450 --> 00:26:36,143
That's close to
$8 million already.

389
00:26:37,261 --> 00:26:39,214
I don't think
you <i>get</i> conditions.

390
00:26:39,518 --> 00:26:42,092
We'll make you a partner
if you can deliver by Sunday.

391
00:26:42,667 --> 00:26:43,771
Sunday?

392
00:26:44,252 --> 00:26:46,476
We'll leave the name
and the title as a goal.

393
00:26:47,175 --> 00:26:48,741
Like it or not,
that works with you.

394
00:26:50,683 --> 00:26:52,134
I'd like to say
I'll think about it,

395
00:26:52,135 --> 00:26:55,459
but I don't think
that's an option, is it?

396
00:27:02,582 --> 00:27:03,872
I'm not really sick.

397
00:27:08,184 --> 00:27:09,193
Welcome aboard.

398
00:27:13,850 --> 00:27:17,498
- Good night, Trudy.
- Good night, gentlemen.

399
00:27:18,021 --> 00:27:21,579
- What if I come up short?
- That's not an option.

400
00:27:23,125 --> 00:27:24,132
Good night.

401
00:27:30,565 --> 00:27:32,820
I want you to call
Hubert Adams as Secor.

402
00:27:33,656 --> 00:27:34,666
His number's in my Rolodex.

403
00:27:34,667 --> 00:27:37,758
I threw it under the bed.
Try him at home.

404
00:27:38,360 --> 00:27:40,266
Tell him I'll meet him
at the St. Regis at 7:30

405
00:27:40,267 --> 00:27:41,869
and sound like
a secretary.

406
00:27:42,801 --> 00:27:44,079
I have to get dressed.

407
00:27:50,926 --> 00:27:52,543
I can't believe
he was gonna leave.

408
00:27:52,813 --> 00:27:53,875
That little shit.

409
00:27:57,188 --> 00:27:59,039
Look, they still have
a picture of Kennedy up.

410
00:28:00,962 --> 00:28:02,484
Although, what are
they gonna do,

411
00:28:02,524 --> 00:28:04,508
take it down and put
up Lyndon Johnson?

412
00:28:06,617 --> 00:28:07,890
Not in this place.

413
00:28:09,379 --> 00:28:12,173
I've acted like I've started
a business my whole life,

414
00:28:12,174 --> 00:28:13,725
but I inherited it.

415
00:28:17,221 --> 00:28:18,279
I need an attorney.

416
00:28:21,601 --> 00:28:22,717
Divorce.

417
00:28:24,190 --> 00:28:25,558
So it's true, huh?

418
00:28:27,944 --> 00:28:30,719
- What are you talking about?
- Henry Francis.

419
00:28:33,162 --> 00:28:36,579
- Who?
- Jesus.

420
00:28:38,598 --> 00:28:40,155
Right when things
were almost normal.

421
00:28:40,783 --> 00:28:43,382
I need you to tell me
what you know.

422
00:28:43,924 --> 00:28:45,500
Margaret's friends
with his daughter.

423
00:28:47,247 --> 00:28:50,014
- Are they sleeping together?
- <i>I don't know.</i>

424
00:28:52,093 --> 00:28:53,791
It came
from his daughter.

425
00:28:54,392 --> 00:28:56,290
He talks about her.

426
00:28:57,726 --> 00:28:59,750
<i>It sounds like</i>
<i>it's serious.</i>

427
00:29:00,748 --> 00:29:01,840
I was gonna tell you--

428
00:29:02,630 --> 00:29:03,675
No, I wasn't.

429
00:29:03,943 --> 00:29:05,186
I thought you <i>knew.</i>

430
00:29:07,675 --> 00:29:09,044
I'm sorry I told you.

431
00:29:10,081 --> 00:29:11,225
Believe me.

432
00:29:25,989 --> 00:29:27,386
I'm sorry about that.

433
00:29:36,831 --> 00:29:40,876
- Wake up.
- Shh, he's sleeping.

434
00:29:40,877 --> 00:29:43,400
I don't care.
Who the hell is Henry Francis?

435
00:29:47,880 --> 00:29:48,896
No one.

436
00:29:50,064 --> 00:29:52,911
Stop it.
Stop it!

437
00:29:52,912 --> 00:29:56,229
- Who the hell is he?
- Why do you care?

438
00:29:56,315 --> 00:29:59,556
Because you're good and
everyone else in the world is bad.

439
00:29:59,638 --> 00:30:00,460
You're drunk.

440
00:30:00,461 --> 00:30:05,312
You're so hurt, so brave with
your little white nose in the air.

441
00:30:05,313 --> 00:30:07,712
All along you've been
building a life raft.

442
00:30:07,844 --> 00:30:08,907
Get out.

443
00:30:09,847 --> 00:30:12,712
- You never forgave me.
- Forgave what?

444
00:30:14,472 --> 00:30:16,021
That I've never
been enough?

445
00:30:16,022 --> 00:30:19,242
You got everything
you ever wanted-- Everything!

446
00:30:19,243 --> 00:30:20,292
And you loved it.

447
00:30:20,438 --> 00:30:23,313
And now I'm not good enough for
some spoiled mainline brat?

448
00:30:23,314 --> 00:30:24,405
That's right!

449
00:30:26,663 --> 00:30:28,497
You won't get a nickel.

450
00:30:29,898 --> 00:30:31,635
And I'll take the kids.

451
00:30:32,401 --> 00:30:34,269
God knows
they'll be better off.

452
00:30:34,643 --> 00:30:38,592
I'm going to Reno, you're going
to consent and that's the end of this.

453
00:30:38,753 --> 00:30:42,636
Don't threaten me.
I know all about you.

454
00:30:45,112 --> 00:30:46,192
You're a whore.

455
00:30:49,520 --> 00:30:50,690
You know that?

456
00:31:11,191 --> 00:31:12,358
I want you out
of the house.

457
00:31:24,826 --> 00:31:25,886
Hold the elevator.

458
00:31:32,334 --> 00:31:34,743
- They called you in, too?
- Yes, they did.

459
00:31:40,391 --> 00:31:44,761
- I'll admit it-- I'm a little scared.
- Of what?

460
00:31:46,706 --> 00:31:49,509
- Why are you here?
- I don't know.

461
00:31:49,617 --> 00:31:50,627
Cooper called me.

462
00:31:51,239 --> 00:31:53,112
First they're cleaning the carpets,
now they're not.

463
00:31:53,845 --> 00:31:58,274
- Why are you here?
- Um, work.

464
00:32:03,343 --> 00:32:05,465
Hey, everybody,
Harry Crane is here.

465
00:32:07,363 --> 00:32:09,172
Relax, Pete,
we're expecting him.

466
00:32:09,925 --> 00:32:11,760
- What's going on?
- Why are you here?

467
00:32:13,938 --> 00:32:15,993
I'm sorry,
what's going on?

468
00:32:17,283 --> 00:32:20,214
P.P.L. has been sold to McCann.
We're starting a new agency.

469
00:32:20,282 --> 00:32:23,267
We'd like you to join us
as our new head of media.

470
00:32:26,488 --> 00:32:28,699
- Are you kidding?
- Yes. Yes, we are.

471
00:32:28,753 --> 00:32:29,876
Happy birthday.

472
00:32:31,394 --> 00:32:32,608
We need your answer.

473
00:32:35,883 --> 00:32:37,449
I should really
call my wife.

474
00:32:37,695 --> 00:32:39,472
Mr. Crane-- Harry,

475
00:32:40,573 --> 00:32:44,158
this matter is secret
and time sensitive.

476
00:32:44,159 --> 00:32:47,164
If you turned us down
and elect to be

477
00:32:47,165 --> 00:32:51,355
a mid-level cog
at McCann Erickson,

478
00:32:52,023 --> 00:32:55,967
we'll have to lock you in
the storeroom until morning.

479
00:32:57,504 --> 00:32:59,417
I'm sure you understand.

480
00:33:01,818 --> 00:33:02,888
Pete.

481
00:33:03,520 --> 00:33:05,492
We were hoping you could
decipher these job sheets.

482
00:33:05,493 --> 00:33:07,234
Where exactly
are these materials?

483
00:33:08,146 --> 00:33:09,326
I never look at these.

484
00:33:12,950 --> 00:33:14,123
Can't we just
take everything?

485
00:33:15,927 --> 00:33:18,594
<i>That's good thinking, but
we don't know where anything is.</i>

486
00:33:18,823 --> 00:33:20,829
No one knows
how this works?

487
00:33:21,430 --> 00:33:22,815
Let me make a phone call.

488
00:33:23,038 --> 00:33:25,114
- I'll take care of this.
- No. No more conspirators.

489
00:33:25,115 --> 00:33:26,358
I'll be discreet.

490
00:33:30,177 --> 00:33:31,187
Where's Don?

491
00:33:36,975 --> 00:33:38,675
What did we do?

492
00:33:40,363 --> 00:33:41,477
Nothing.

493
00:33:41,927 --> 00:33:44,513
Then why are we
in the living room?

494
00:33:46,675 --> 00:33:48,719
We want to tell
you something because--

495
00:33:50,259 --> 00:33:53,403
Well, it's going to be
a little bit of a change.

496
00:33:53,988 --> 00:33:56,061
Your father is going
to be moving out.

497
00:33:59,524 --> 00:34:04,378
Now, we'll still be living here
and he'll come to visit.

498
00:34:06,055 --> 00:34:07,503
Then why is he going?

499
00:34:08,919 --> 00:34:09,968
Because...

500
00:34:16,445 --> 00:34:17,892
It'll just be temporary.

501
00:34:18,833 --> 00:34:20,677
Like when you lived
in the hotel?

502
00:34:21,271 --> 00:34:23,204
- Yes.
- It'll be different.

503
00:34:27,776 --> 00:34:32,047
- Is it because I lost your cufflinks?
- No, it has nothing to do with you.

504
00:34:35,368 --> 00:34:36,378
That's not what I mean.

505
00:34:40,257 --> 00:34:42,985
I love you both.
You know that.

506
00:34:43,463 --> 00:34:44,883
Then why are you going?

507
00:34:47,540 --> 00:34:48,701
I'm not going.

508
00:34:51,102 --> 00:34:54,402
I'm just...
living elsewhere.

509
00:34:54,403 --> 00:34:57,725
That's going. You say things
and you don't mean them.

510
00:34:57,726 --> 00:35:01,133
- You can't just do that.
- Sally, sweetheart--

511
00:35:01,853 --> 00:35:03,915
- Go away.
- Sally, stop it.

512
00:35:05,788 --> 00:35:07,863
You said you'd always
come home.

513
00:35:11,649 --> 00:35:12,752
I will.

514
00:35:15,165 --> 00:35:16,788
It's just
a different home.

515
00:35:20,312 --> 00:35:24,789
- Will you be here for Christmas?
- You'll get to have two Christmases.

516
00:35:24,790 --> 00:35:26,500
I only want one.

517
00:35:27,201 --> 00:35:28,914
Did you make him leave?

518
00:35:30,856 --> 00:35:33,262
No. We both decided.

519
00:35:33,263 --> 00:35:36,305
You made him sleep in Gene's room,
and it's scary in there.

520
00:35:36,306 --> 00:35:37,613
Listen to me,
both of you.

521
00:35:39,665 --> 00:35:40,712
I will be here.

522
00:35:41,307 --> 00:35:43,856
You can call me, I will
answer and I will be here.

523
00:35:43,857 --> 00:35:47,135
- Sally. Sally.
- Let her go.

524
00:35:47,745 --> 00:35:51,015
Please don't go.
I don't want you to.

525
00:36:01,475 --> 00:36:02,971
Nobody wants
to do this.

526
00:36:06,739 --> 00:36:08,663
I need you
to be a big boy.

527
00:36:31,808 --> 00:36:35,269
- You look awful.
- Can I come in?

528
00:36:48,989 --> 00:36:50,768
Do you want anything?

529
00:36:53,069 --> 00:36:54,208
Yes, I do.

530
00:36:58,639 --> 00:36:59,754
You were right.

531
00:37:04,068 --> 00:37:08,341
I've taken you for granted
and I've been hard on you,

532
00:37:10,930 --> 00:37:15,572
but only because I think I see you
as an extension of myself.

533
00:37:18,654 --> 00:37:19,786
And you're not.

534
00:37:21,586 --> 00:37:23,741
Well, thank you
for stopping by.

535
00:37:23,742 --> 00:37:26,849
Please. Sit down.

536
00:37:36,618 --> 00:37:38,819
Do you know why I don't
want to go to McCann?

537
00:37:39,547 --> 00:37:41,636
Because you can't work
for anyone else.

538
00:37:43,265 --> 00:37:44,295
No.

539
00:37:47,014 --> 00:37:49,821
Because there are people
out there who buy things,

540
00:37:50,594 --> 00:37:52,277
People like you and me,

541
00:37:54,078 --> 00:37:55,868
And something happened--

542
00:37:57,769 --> 00:37:59,743
Something terrible.

543
00:38:03,357 --> 00:38:05,755
And the way that
they saw themselves...

544
00:38:10,712 --> 00:38:11,850
Is gone.

545
00:38:18,015 --> 00:38:19,713
And nobody
understands that.

546
00:38:23,637 --> 00:38:24,825
But you do.

547
00:38:29,405 --> 00:38:31,186
And that's very valuable.

548
00:38:35,092 --> 00:38:36,279
Is it?

549
00:38:39,530 --> 00:38:42,245
With you or without you,
I'm moving on.

550
00:38:46,988 --> 00:38:48,856
And I don't know
if I can do it alone.

551
00:38:53,114 --> 00:38:54,386
Will you help me?

552
00:39:03,998 --> 00:39:05,545
What if I say no?

553
00:39:07,946 --> 00:39:10,438
You'll never speak
to me again.

554
00:39:13,780 --> 00:39:14,903
No.

555
00:39:16,904 --> 00:39:19,808
I will spend the rest of 
my life trying to hire you.

556
00:39:32,836 --> 00:39:34,867
Mrs. Harris, what a 
pleasure to see you.

557
00:39:36,493 --> 00:39:39,194
- What is she doing here?
- I said I'd be discreet.

558
00:39:39,873 --> 00:39:41,217
Tell them what to do.

559
00:39:41,218 --> 00:39:43,421
I made a list and I 
called some movers.

560
00:39:43,422 --> 00:39:45,632
Can you read these? Do 
you know where this stuff is?

561
00:39:45,633 --> 00:39:48,930
Yes. Of course you'll need the 
job bags on all these accounts.

562
00:39:48,931 --> 00:39:51,900
We'll also need logo files,
all the film we can find

563
00:39:51,901 --> 00:39:54,196
And negatives which
aren't actually here.

564
00:39:54,371 --> 00:39:55,246
There you go.

565
00:39:55,247 --> 00:40:00,624
- Very good. Now I can pack.
- Sorry I'm late.

566
00:40:01,635 --> 00:40:02,681
Hi.

567
00:40:04,096 --> 00:40:05,138
Joan.

568
00:40:05,259 --> 00:40:06,463
What a good idea.

569
00:40:07,719 --> 00:40:09,355
Well, you're here.
Who did you bring?

570
00:40:09,494 --> 00:40:13,513
North American aviation, 
Secor, Jai alai, samsonite.

571
00:40:14,246 --> 00:40:16,606
- Clearasil.
- Really?

572
00:40:17,635 --> 00:40:18,801
I made it.

573
00:40:19,653 --> 00:40:20,868
Where do we start?

574
00:40:21,047 --> 00:40:22,995
Well, I'd start
in the art department.

575
00:40:23,034 --> 00:40:24,306
It's locked.

576
00:40:32,205 --> 00:40:33,389
Great.

577
00:40:38,610 --> 00:40:40,141
I'll start
in my office..

578
00:40:44,318 --> 00:40:45,727
Joanie, I can't read
your writing.

579
00:40:47,802 --> 00:40:50,796
It's perfectly clear--
"correspondence.

580
00:40:54,400 --> 00:40:55,680
Oh, I'm tired.

581
00:40:56,597 --> 00:41:00,008
- Peggy, can you get me some coffee?
- No.

582
00:41:03,729 --> 00:41:05,504
Did you wash your hands?

583
00:41:08,412 --> 00:41:09,708
Hold the elevator.

584
00:41:12,568 --> 00:41:14,117
Greg is going to kill me.

585
00:41:15,105 --> 00:41:18,098
I'm at the Roosevelt, but I'll 
need you to find me an apartment.

586
00:41:18,214 --> 00:41:20,896
- Furnished?
- For the time being.

587
00:41:21,198 --> 00:41:23,872
Sorry. Good night.

588
00:41:31,915 --> 00:41:32,960
Go ahead, fellas.

589
00:41:47,247 --> 00:41:50,123
How long do you think it'll take 
us to be in a place like this again?

590
00:41:52,994 --> 00:41:55,506
I never saw myself working
in a place like this.

591
00:42:12,622 --> 00:42:13,894
Don't bother.

592
00:42:34,025 --> 00:42:35,593
We've been robbed!

593
00:42:37,293 --> 00:42:40,309
He's waiting on the line.
It's his third attempt.

594
00:42:42,713 --> 00:42:44,588
Saint John, how are you?

595
00:42:44,589 --> 00:42:47,533
What in god's name is
going on over there?

596
00:42:47,534 --> 00:42:49,878
I think at this point
it should be very clear.

597
00:42:50,856 --> 00:42:52,063
You're fired.

598
00:42:52,185 --> 00:42:54,808
You're fired for costing this 
company millions of pounds.

599
00:42:54,809 --> 00:42:56,653
You're fired for insubordination!

600
00:42:56,654 --> 00:42:59,456
You're fired
for lack of character!

601
00:42:59,457 --> 00:43:01,605
Very good. Happy Christmas.

602
00:43:02,497 --> 00:43:05,996
Mr. Hooker. I've been sacked.

603
00:43:05,997 --> 00:43:08,856
Please have my office and things 
put in storage at this address.

604
00:43:08,857 --> 00:43:12,969
- What's happened?
- You're a sharp boy. You'll figure 
  it out.

605
00:43:14,685 --> 00:43:18,830
So let's see. I have Peggy 
and Pete sharing the desk.

606
00:43:18,831 --> 00:43:20,815
Don, we'll replace
one of these couches

607
00:43:20,816 --> 00:43:23,936
With a table for you, and we're 
adding two additional phone lines.

608
00:43:23,937 --> 00:43:26,558
Media will be in the bedroom
with the television.

609
00:43:26,559 --> 00:43:28,185
Accounts gets the bed.

610
00:43:29,049 --> 00:43:31,240
And no one is to come
to this office.

611
00:43:31,241 --> 00:43:33,562
If you have meetings,
please take them elsewhere.

612
00:43:33,563 --> 00:43:37,450
I don't want them in the 
lobby or the bar of this hotel.

613
00:43:40,045 --> 00:43:41,278
Well, look at that.

614
00:43:45,114 --> 00:43:48,675
Good morning. Sterling Cooper Draper Pryce. How may I help you?

615
00:43:51,317 --> 00:43:54,218
Yes, Harry, it's room 435.

616
00:43:56,553 --> 00:43:59,411
He didn't leave a note-- 
Nothing.

617
00:43:59,412 --> 00:44:00,534
Where is he?

618
00:44:00,685 --> 00:44:04,278
I just heard from John Deere--
Pete tried to poach them on Saturday.

619
00:44:04,439 --> 00:44:06,016
He must have gone with Draper.

620
00:44:15,517 --> 00:44:16,685
Damn it.

621
00:44:18,314 --> 00:44:23,397
Sure. Everything is exactly the same.
Don and I will both be on the account.

622
00:44:24,364 --> 00:44:27,203
Thanks, Bill. Okay, bye bye.

623
00:44:28,587 --> 00:44:31,156
- Hello, everybody.
- Lovely, what are you doing here?

624
00:44:31,157 --> 00:44:35,317
I brought lunch. There's every 
kind of sandwich imaginable and a cake.

625
00:44:35,513 --> 00:44:36,646
Thank you, Trudy.

626
00:44:36,647 --> 00:44:39,512
- Isn't this exciting?
- It is.

627
00:44:41,113 --> 00:44:43,281
This looks great, Trudy.

628
00:44:47,713 --> 00:44:49,566
- There's food.
- Thank god.

629
00:45:04,761 --> 00:45:06,216
Draper residence.

630
00:45:09,182 --> 00:45:10,246
It's me.

631
00:45:15,392 --> 00:45:18,248
I'm not sure where I'm staying right now,
but I'll be working out of the Pierre.

632
00:45:21,213 --> 00:45:22,280
Okay.

633
00:45:26,478 --> 00:45:31,215
Listen, betts, I want you to know
I'm not going to fight you.

634
00:45:36,197 --> 00:45:37,320
Thank you.

635
00:45:41,033 --> 00:45:42,852
I hope you get what 
you always wanted.

636
00:45:47,549 --> 00:45:49,291
You will always be their father.

637
00:45:54,971 --> 00:45:56,046
Okay.

638
00:45:58,654 --> 00:46:02,209
Well, goodbye.

639
00:46:05,910 --> 00:46:07,246
Goodbye.

640
00:46:24,531 --> 00:46:28,574
You know, if you leave your shoes outside the door here, somebody polishes them.

641
00:46:29,286 --> 00:46:30,369
Hello, don.

642
00:46:31,443 --> 00:46:32,608
How was your morning?

643
00:46:33,075 --> 00:46:34,489
Very productive.

